- "Cumulative metric count" is the sum of metric counts for each level, ordered by the number of metrics.

- "blossomed with multiple metrics" refers to experiments that have more than one performance metric;
- "positive average discounted return" refers to experiments where the average discounted return is greater than 0;
- "peak performance" refers to the maximum return (`max_return`) of the experiment.

